            {
              "type": "prose",
              "iaja": "I",
              "text": "The numbers at Triaging tell a mix-shift story rather than an absolute-growth story. Group organic was roughly flat in 2025 as Fibre Solutions declined ~5% on overcapacity, offset by DC +37% and HE +11%. What matters is that DC+HE are now a third of sales but ~60% of adjusted EBITA — the legacy business has become dilutive both to growth and to margin."
            },
            {
              "type": "prose",
              "iaja": "J",
              "ratings": [
                {
                  "grade": "B",
                  "attr": "financial quality"
                }
              ],
              "text": "Financials rate B at Triaging. Not outstanding — the FTTH legacy business is still absorbing working capital (104 DIO) and the performance programme is in early stages. But the mix shift is quantified, the DC unit economics are genuinely asset-light, and there is no cash-generation red flag. Worth ESA depth."
            }
