              "text": "Outputs are a classic mix-shift read. Nothing A-rated because the group is still cycle-depressed; nothing below B except the balance sheet which is acquisition-funded. The interesting line is 4.9 (returns on incremental capital) — DC services is genuinely asset-light with ~1% capex and 12-14% NWC, which drops incremental ROIC meaningfully above the group average."
